President Obama expressed gratitude towards legislators and advocates for their work on H.R. 2094, a bill aimed at making EpiPens more accessible in schools. The President shared that his daughter, Malia, has a peanut allergy, and emphasized the importance of having EpiPens available for emergencies. He commended the bipartisan efforts and advocacy communities for their work, and announced that states will receive increased incentives to ensure the availability of EpiPens in schools.